  .","post-medieval variant of   Maiden  , with excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Marsters","meanings":["English: variant of   Masters  . <i>Marsters</i> is the predominant surname on Palmerston Island, Cook Islands, South Pacific, deriving from a settler and owner reputedly born in Leicestershire."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs John Masters was born in 1503, in England, United Kingdom. She married John Masters in 1522, in Somerset, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 daughters."},"et":{"1503–":"1503–Surnud","1503–1579":"1503–1579","1523–1586":"1523–1586","1535–Female":"1535–Surnud","1546–Female":"1546–Surnud","1503–Female":"1503–Surnud","1503":"1503","1546":"1546","1535":"1535","1579":"1579","1523":"1523","1522":"1522","1586":"1586","about 1535":"umbes 1535","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tintinhull, South Somerset district, Somerset, England":"Tintinhull, Somerset, England","Tintinhull, Somerset, England":"Tintinhull, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","North Petherton, Somerset, England":"North Petherton, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1503–":"1503–Kuollut","1503–1579":"1503–1579","1523–1586":"1523–1586","1535–Female":"1535–Kuollut","1546–Female":"1546–Kuollut","1503–Female":"1503–Kuollut","1503":"1503","1546":"1546","1535":"1535","1579":"1579","1523":"1523","1522":"1522","1586":"1586","about 1535":"noin 1535","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Tintinhull, South Somerset district, Somerset, England":"Tintinhull, Somerset, England","Tintinhull, Somerset, England":"Tintinhull, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti,